cards.name: Design new template for index pages of PA/GEO pages.
cards.desc:
Come up with a design for a new page template that will be shown on the index page of each folder. (eg. /car-accidents/, /anaheim/)

The design should contain the following: 
- Hero Image (with customizable text)
- Contact form near the top
- Section for displaying case results relating to that category
- Section for displaying reviews
- Section for videos
- Section for blogs
- Multiple sections for content (in the same way that the homepage has multiple sections for content, we can segregate different categories of content into the different sections

Some notes/thoughts:

The template should allow for us to take out any of these sections without breaking anything. (to a certain extent. For example, you should be able to get rid of at least 1 content section but you don't have to get rid of all of them. If you've put 2 sections right next to each other you might have to get rid of both of them to make it look right, etc.)

Design mobile first and then move to desktop? Potentially we might not want to show every single section on the mobile version because it might be too overwhelming? Or move some sections to the bottom?

Allow for other customize-able images in the content, or in the background?
